column28:
Design: Make sure the label is Green

Manufacturing: Mix the formula really well
column31: Watering Can: Add 2 Tbs (30mL) per gallon of water. Hose End Sprayer: Set dial to 1 oz (30mL) setting. Spring & Summer: Apply every 1–2 weeks. Fall & Winter: Apply every 4 weeks. Leaf Misting (Optional): Add 1 tsp per quart (32 oz) of water. Spray on leaves. Apply every 1–2 weeks.
column32: Soil: Try a well-draining soil, with some water retention. Watering: Moderate to high watering with soil mostly dry between waterings. Lighting: Generally, cherry trees prefer direct, bright light.

column75: Cherry Tree Fertilizer for Cherry Trees, Great for Bing, Rainier, and Montmorency Varieties, Liquid Fertilizer by TPS Plant Foods, 8 oz (250mL)
column76:
• Designed specifically for cherry trees, from flowering to harvest

• Boosts vibrant blooms, strong roots, and productive fruit production

• Liquid formula for easy, even feeding with fast absorption

• Made in the USA
column77:
There’s nothing quite like the sight of cherry blossoms or the taste of freshly picked cherries from your own backyard. Our Cherry Tree Fertilizer is crafted to help you get the most out of your trees—from springtime blooms to summer fruit harvests. Whether you’re growing sweet, sour, or ornamental cherry trees, this fertilizer delivers the nutrients needed for full, healthy growth.

With a balanced NPK formula plus essential micronutrients, this liquid fertilizer encourages early flowering, strengthens root systems, and promotes abundant fruiting. It’s easy to apply with a watering can or sprayer, and it absorbs quickly to deliver fast, visible results. Use it throughout the growing season to support your trees at every stage—from first bud to final fruit.

Whether you have a single backyard tree or a small orchard, Cherry Tree Fertilizer makes care simple and results spectacular. It's the ideal choice for home gardeners who want more blossoms, tastier fruit, and healthier trees. Feed your cherry tree the right way—and enjoy a sweeter harvest season after season.
